# Go Rules — Discursive

## Project Structure (target)

```
main.go             # Cobra CLI entry (thin main → cli.Execute)
internal/
├── config/         # AppSettings, paths, load/save
├── crypto/         # Moonshot + DeepSeek secret protect + gateway key gen
├── gateway/        # HTTP server, auth, sanitizer, optimizer, multi-provider proxy
├── tunnel/         # cloudflared supervise + BYO public URL
├── usage/          # pricing table + per-session token/cost store
└── doctor/         # health checks aggregating the above
```

- Prefer small packages with a **package comment** stating responsibility and a
  one-line **Contract** (what it may / must not depend on).
- Reference behavior: `examples/use-kimi-on-cursor/src-tauri/` — reimplement in
  Go; never vendor Rust/TS into the product tree.
- CLI: **Cobra** — see `.cursor/rules/cobra.mdc`. No Viper for MVP.

## Logging — `log/slog` (required)

- All product logging uses Go stdlib **`log/slog`**.
- Do not add logrus/zap unless the user explicitly asks.
- Structured attrs for gateway/usage: `session_id`, `provider`, `model`,
  `tokens_in`, `tokens_out`, `cache_hit_tokens`, `cache_miss_tokens`, `est_usd`,
  `request_id`, `latency_ms`. Per-call `usage` is **DEBUG**; idle `usage_summary`
  is **INFO** (`DISCURSIVE_LOG_LEVEL`, default info).
- CLI emits slog JSON on **stdout** (not stderr) so operators can pipe:
  `go run . start | jq .`
- **Never** put API keys, gateway secrets, or raw Authorization headers in slog
  attributes or messages.
- Background mode (`--background`) writes slog to a rotating log file via
  `util.SetupLoggerToWriter(w, level)` **after** `daemon.Detach()`, so the
  handler captures the correct writer fd — never through the stale initial
  `os.Stdout` reference.

## Tests (hard AC)

- Package logic with behavior: **table-driven tests** required for new/changed
  exported behavior:
  `tests := []struct{ name string; … }{ … }` + `t.Run(tt.name, …)`.
- Cover success **and** important failure/edge cases.
- No network in unit tests unless the task is explicitly live (`T10` / `-tags=live`).
- Acceptance criteria for Go tasks must include `go test` for touched packages
  (not only `go build`).

## Craft

- Wrap errors with `%w`; return actionable messages at CLI boundaries.
- Auth to Moonshot / DeepSeek: `Authorization: Bearer {key}` only (OpenAI-compat).
  Select key from resolved **provider** in the model map.
- Verify packages with `go test` before wiring CLI; prefer `make verify` when
  Makefile exists.
- **Never suppress linter warnings with `//nolint` comments.** Fix the root
  cause instead. The only exception is generated code (`*.pb.go`, `*_string.go`).

## Inspiration directive (hard)

- Product Go source and comments must **never** mention Claude Code or imply we
  ship/vendor third-party agent source.
- Never copy `examples/use-kimi-on-cursor` into the product module path; port
  behavior.
- Do not vendor `examples/openai-openapi/` into the binary.

### `slog secrets leak`

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
| ----- | ---- | ----- |
| Key material appears in logs or diagnostics | Logging request headers or config dumps wholesale | Log only masked prefixes; redact known secret fields |

### `Missing table-driven coverage`

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
| ----- | ---- | ----- |
| New package behavior ships with only a smoke/`go build` check | Treated tests as optional | Add `[]struct{ name string; … }` + `t.Run` for success and edge cases before AC pass |

### `JSON stdout + interactive stderr clash`

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
| ----- | ---- | ----- |
| Structured slog JSON lines interleave with interactive TUI prompts, breaking both the visual flow for the user and `| jq .` pipe consumers | slog writes to stdout (default) while interactive UI also writes to stdout; the two streams intermix | Redirect interactive prompts to stderr; wrap interactive sections by replacing the default slog handler with one writing to `io.Discard`, then restoring on `defer` |

